---
layout: base.njk
title: Improvlore - Bangalore
showCustomEvents: false
---
{% from "badges.njk" import posterBadges %}
{% from "cards.njk" import formatCard with context %}

<div class="events-root">

  {# Hero answers "who are you / is this for me / where do I go" for a new
     visitor, while keeping a fast path into events. The featured card shows
     the single next upcoming event of any type, with a copy fallback if
     nothing is scheduled so the hero never renders half-empty. #}
  {% set heroNext = filters.nextEvent(events, showCustomEvents) %}

  <section class="home-hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <div class="home-hero-intro">
      <p class="home-hero-eyebrow">Improv in Bangalore and beyond, since 2022</p>
      <p class="fun-shout" aria-hidden="true"><span class="fun-f">F</span><span class="fun-u">U</span><span class="fun-n">N</span></p>
      <h1 class="home-hero-heading" id="hero-heading">Live theatre, made up on the spot.</h1>
      <p class="home-hero-lede">No script, no second take. We build shows from your suggestions, then never do them again. Come watch, jump into a jam, or learn it yourself.</p>
      <div class="home-hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/events/">See what's on</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    {% if heroNext %}
    {% set heroType = filters.eventType(heroNext.title, heroNext.tags) %}
    {# Card body is a plain container, not a link, so the Buy Ticket button can
       live inside it. The title is a "stretched link" (::after covers the whole
       card) so the card still clicks through to the detail page, while the Buy
       button sits above it with its own click. #}
    <div class="home-hero-next event-type-{{ heroType }}">
      <img class="home-hero-next-poster" src="{{ filters.eventImage(heroNext) }}" alt="{{ filters.workshopName(heroNext.title) }} poster" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" sizes="(min-width: 760px) 420px, 100vw">
      <div class="home-hero-next-body">
        <span class="home-hero-next-kicker">Up next</span>
        <span class="event-type-badge">{{ heroType }}</span>
        {{ posterBadges(filters.eventBadges(heroNext.title), heroType, true) }}
        <a class="home-hero-next-title home-hero-next-stretch" href="{{ filters.eventPermalink(heroNext) }}">{{ filters.workshopName(heroNext.title) }}</a>
        {% set heroSessions = filters.eventSessions(heroNext.title) %}
        <div class="event-when home-hero-when">
          <span class="event-when-cal">
            <span class="event-when-dow">{{ filters.formatDay(heroNext.event_starts_at) }}</span>
            <span class="event-when-day">{{ filters.formatDayNum(heroNext.event_starts_at) }}</span>
            <span class="event-when-mon">{{ filters.formatMonth(heroNext.event_starts_at) }}</span>
          </span>
          <span class="event-when-detail">
            <span class="event-when-date">{{ filters.formatDateFull(heroNext.event_starts_at) }}</span>
            <span class="event-when-time">{{ filters.formatTime(heroNext.event_starts_at) }}</span>
            {% if heroSessions and heroSessions.dates and heroSessions.dates.length > 1 %}<span class="home-hero-next-tag">+{{ heroSessions.dates.length - 1 }} more dates</span>{% endif %}
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="event-buttons home-hero-next-cta">
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" {% if "district.in" in heroNext.url %}data-ticket-slug {% endif %}href="{{ heroNext.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy Ticket</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% else %}
    {# Nothing on the live feed (between listings, or the fetch failed). Keep the
       hero balanced with a quiet card pointing to where shows live, instead of
       leaving the column empty or blanking the whole page. #}
    <a class="home-hero-next home-hero-next-empty" href="/library/">
      <span class="home-hero-next-body">
        <span class="home-hero-next-kicker">What we run</span>
        <span class="home-hero-next-title">Shows, jams, and workshops</span>
        <span class="home-hero-next-blurb">Nothing on the public calendar this minute. Browse every format we run, and check back soon for dates.</span>
      </span>
    </a>
    {% endif %}
  </section>

  <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="section-start">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-start">New Here? Start Anywhere</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">However you like to play, there's a way in. We just want you to find joy in play again.</p>

    <ul class="book-offer-list about-paths">
      <li>
        <a class="about-path-link" href="/events/?type=show">
          <strong>Watch a show</strong>
          <p>Sit back and let us build a one-time-only show from your suggestions. Nothing for you to do but enjoy it.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="about-path-link" href="/events/?type=jam">
          <strong>Play at a jam</strong>
          <p>Our open, beginner-friendly sessions. Jump in, mess around, meet people. No experience needed.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="about-path-link" href="/events/?type=workshop">
          <strong>Take a workshop</strong>
          <p>Learn by doing, at a pace that's kind to first-timers. A guided room where it's safe to try.</p>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="book-cta-line">Pricing and venue are listed on each event, so you always know before you go.</p>
  </section>

  <p class="yesand-shout" aria-hidden="true"><span class="yesand-yes">WHIM</span><span class="yesand-and">SY</span></p>

  <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="section-about">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-about">Who We Are</h2>

    <div class="about-intro">
      <p class="about-lede">A Bangalore improv troupe since 2022, now playing festivals across Asia. The same group of people you'll meet at a jam, hosting a workshop, or on stage at a show.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="more-line">
      <a href="/about/">Read our story →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  {# Festivals were only a one-line text mention before. Surfaced here as a
     proper section (stat band + compact timeline) so the touring story is
     visible on the home page, with the full account on /festivals/. The
     timeline reuses the same data + markup as the festivals page so the two
     never drift. #}
  <section class="page-section home-fest" aria-labelledby="section-fest">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-fest">On the Road</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">A Bangalore troupe, but the shows travel. Since 2024 we've been invited to improv festivals across Asia.</p>

    <ul class="about-stats" aria-label="Improv Lore festivals at a glance">
      <li>
        <span class="about-stat-num">4</span>
        <span class="about-stat-label">Festivals played</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="about-stat-num">4</span>
        <span class="about-stat-label">Cities abroad</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="about-stat-num">2024</span>
        <span class="about-stat-label">First trip out</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <ol class="fest-timeline home-fest-timeline" aria-label="Festivals Improv Lore has played">
      {% for fest in festivals %}
      <li class="fest-stop">
        <span class="fest-stop-year">{{ fest.year }}</span>
        <div class="fest-stop-body">
          <strong>{{ fest.name }}</strong>
          <p><span class="fest-stop-city">{{ fest.city }}</span><span class="fest-stop-when">{{ fest.when }}</span></p>
        </div>
      </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ol>

    <p class="more-line">
      Singapore, Vietnam, Manila, Hong Kong, and counting.
      <a href="/festivals/">See where we've played →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="section-shows">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-shows">Shows We Are Known For</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Built live from what the room gives us, so no two are the same. A taste of the formats we keep coming back to.</p>

    {# Home shows a curated few and defers to the Library for the full set, so the
       grids don't repeat verbatim across Home / About / Library. The cap is done
       in the data layer (filters.firstOfType) because this Nunjucks build's
       selectattr/slice filters don't actually filter. The Library is canonical. #}
    <ul class="about-shows" aria-label="Signature show formats">
      {% for fmt in filters.firstOfType(catalog, "show", 3) %}{{ formatCard(fmt) }}{% endfor %}
    </ul>

    <p class="more-line">
      That's just a few. Every show, jam, and workshop we run lives in
      <a href="/library/">the library →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section page-section-info" aria-labelledby="section-more">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-more">More From Us</h2>

    <a class="corporate-banner" href="/for-teams/">
      <span class="corporate-banner-text">
        <strong>We bring improv to workplaces too.</strong>
        Custom shows and team workshops, shaped around your team.
      </span>
      <span class="corporate-banner-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
  </section>

</div>
